pullRequest.body:
Define the map of a PartialEquiv through an embedding, and related properties.
Define embeddings and equivalences between equal structures or equal substructures, and related properties.
Add miscellaneous lemmas which will be used to prove the existence of fraisse limits.

---

This is preparation for #18876

Opening a PR for all the preliminary stuff that your end theorem needs is an easy trap to fall into. It results in big PRs doing many too things at once that wait forever in review.

I would finger-guess that reviewing time is roughly quadratic in the size of the diff, so if you split your 330 lines PR into 4-5 PRs (one per modified file, maybe) of 60-150 lines, you might gain a 20x speedup on review 😉

Yes, that was a mistake, it has been corrected.

```suggestion
/-- Embedding between equal structures. -/
```
and everywhere else

```suggestion
theorem ofEq_toEmbeding (h : M = N) :
    (ofEq h).toEmbedding = Embedding.ofEq h := by
```
